Source: Soil Erosion in New Zealand
Author: CUMBERLAND
Vol / Page: 100
Edition:
Quote: Subcutaneous dimpling appears to be limited to land which, in the course of European occupance, has been ploughed at least once. Under these circumstances dimpling replaces sub-surface sheet wash.
